WEBVTT

00:02.895 --> 00:04.712
♪

00:06.007 --> 00:08.899
[classical music plays]

00:08.901 --> 00:11.401
[announcer]
<i> C-SPAN 5 now takes you</i>
<i> to testimony</i>

00:11.403 --> 00:14.238
<i> before the Joint Committee</i>
<i> on Terrible Events.</i>

00:14.240 --> 00:16.664
[indistinct chatter]

00:17.667 --> 00:20.427
The Chair recognizes the woman
with the four-foot beehive.

00:20.429 --> 00:22.855
Please state your name
and occupation.

00:22.931 --> 00:25.190
Uh, Marjorie Bouvier Simpson.

00:25.267 --> 00:27.175
Mother to three children

00:27.177 --> 00:28.676
and a husband.

00:28.729 --> 00:31.679
She's raising us all on her own.

00:31.757 --> 00:33.315
[Homer whimpering]

00:34.351 --> 00:36.184
Mrs. Simpson,
please walk us through

00:36.262 --> 00:38.595
the events of March 12.

00:38.597 --> 00:41.615
Well, it all started
with what was supposed to be

00:41.691 --> 00:43.375
a happy family trip.

00:43.452 --> 00:47.713
The Simpsons are going
to Pile Ridge, Louisiana.

00:47.790 --> 00:50.457
Oh, the trip is already ruined.

00:50.534 --> 00:52.217
What is this gunk?

00:52.294 --> 00:54.887
Oh, that's my lentil soup.

00:55.038 --> 00:56.555
Lisa!

00:56.557 --> 00:58.615
Well, what else
am I supposed to eat

00:58.617 --> 01:02.119
at your family's
barbaric pig butchery?

01:02.121 --> 01:04.229
It's<i> boucherie.</i>

01:04.231 --> 01:06.623
It's a cherished
Bouvier tradition

01:06.625 --> 01:08.883
that reunites
our extended family

01:08.961 --> 01:11.886
and celebrates our Cajun roots.

01:11.964 --> 01:13.238
And they shoot the pig
in the head,

01:13.315 --> 01:15.966
John Wick-style. Look.

01:15.968 --> 01:17.859
Stop, it's horrifying.

01:17.894 --> 01:20.804
Mmm. Delicious.

01:20.806 --> 01:21.955
[laughs]

01:22.065 --> 01:24.249
[Homer shrieks]
Horrifying!

01:24.326 --> 01:26.493
Mr. Simpson, as I understand it,

01:26.570 --> 01:30.572
you were enticed by the thought
of enjoying savory meats,

01:30.591 --> 01:34.318
but repulsed by the appearance
of your wife's family.

01:34.320 --> 01:36.820
Yes, Senator,
I cannot perjure myself.

01:36.822 --> 01:38.931
They are barf in human form.

01:38.933 --> 01:40.265
I reclaim my time.

01:40.267 --> 01:43.093
Traveling brings out
Homer's worst qualities.

01:44.496 --> 01:48.665
Oh! All the seats are taken by
jerks and their bags.

01:48.667 --> 01:50.867
Maybe we can sit in there.

01:50.869 --> 01:52.194
That looks comfy.

01:53.930 --> 01:55.930
Squirt em' if you got em'.

01:55.932 --> 01:57.858
Oh! [growls]

01:57.934 --> 02:00.602
Your hoops are quivering.
Calm down.

02:00.604 --> 02:03.771
Now boarding:
Active-duty TV clowns.

02:03.849 --> 02:05.290
-[tires screech]
-[Homer yelps]

02:05.367 --> 02:06.350
[sniffing]

02:06.352 --> 02:08.776
Some sober companion you are.

02:08.778 --> 02:10.370
I'm only
three hours out of rehab

02:10.447 --> 02:12.297
and I can smell
the booze on you.

02:12.299 --> 02:14.449
You mean my hand sanitizer?

02:14.526 --> 02:16.593
Ooh, Daddy want!

02:18.455 --> 02:20.213
Mrs. Simpson, we're overbooked.

02:20.290 --> 02:21.789
Your seats are
no longer together.

02:21.867 --> 02:23.033
This is bull!

02:23.035 --> 02:25.535
I demand to speak
to Sully Sullenberger!

02:25.537 --> 02:26.979
Homer, stop it.

02:27.055 --> 02:30.040
You always do this.
You'll get us banned.

02:30.042 --> 02:32.634
So? We'll take
our business elsewh--

02:32.711 --> 02:33.877
[muffled shouting]

02:33.879 --> 02:35.970
There is no elsewhere.

02:36.048 --> 02:37.881
Because of your past behavior,

02:37.883 --> 02:39.491
you're on the No Fly List

02:39.568 --> 02:42.552
of every other airline
in the country.

02:42.554 --> 02:43.871
Even Spirit.

02:43.873 --> 02:45.664
Try it again.

02:45.741 --> 02:47.708
[engine cranking]

02:49.228 --> 02:52.579
So, unless you want
all our future vacations

02:52.731 --> 02:55.916
to be at my mother's house,
talking her into hospice,

02:56.068 --> 02:59.419
you will hold it together
on this flight.

02:59.421 --> 03:01.829
I promise, Marge.
I won't let you down.

03:01.849 --> 03:03.407
I do have some good news.

03:03.425 --> 03:06.259
We have one free upgrade
for a seat in first class.

03:06.261 --> 03:09.095
Ooh, I bet I'd really
keep my promise to behave

03:09.172 --> 03:11.932
if I'm in
that spacious lie-flat pod.

03:11.934 --> 03:13.600
Well, you'll never know.

03:13.677 --> 03:15.110
Yoink.

03:18.607 --> 03:21.683
Uh-uh, sweetie,
first class is this way.

03:21.760 --> 03:22.776
Welcome.

03:22.928 --> 03:23.927
Oh, my God.

03:23.929 --> 03:25.278
I'm turning left.

03:25.355 --> 03:27.781
I didn't know planes had a left.

03:27.933 --> 03:28.916
[gasps]

03:28.918 --> 03:30.542
Ah. Ooh.

03:30.544 --> 03:31.710
[laughs]

03:31.712 --> 03:33.119
♪

03:33.196 --> 03:34.504
[Marge]
Oh...

03:36.884 --> 03:39.626
Oh, the seat
is so plush and comfy.

03:39.628 --> 03:41.035
May I get you anything?

03:41.113 --> 03:42.721
I want everything.

03:42.798 --> 03:45.206
The whole
first class experience.

03:45.284 --> 03:48.876
Cold bubbly,
warm nuts, hot towel...

03:48.954 --> 03:51.137
all the temperatures!

03:51.139 --> 03:54.458
Let's start you out with
a complimentary Moet mimosa

03:54.460 --> 03:56.460
with extra zest and a little--

03:56.462 --> 03:57.569
Oh.

03:57.646 --> 03:59.145
[moans happily]

03:59.222 --> 04:00.739
[snoring lightly]

04:03.727 --> 04:05.469
Okay, Homer, you can do this.

04:05.471 --> 04:08.138
Have a pleasant flight
for Marge.

04:08.140 --> 04:09.155
[overlapping shouts]

04:09.232 --> 04:10.640
-Ow, my head!
-Watch it!

04:10.642 --> 04:11.750
Ow!

04:11.901 --> 04:12.993
[Homer]
<i> God, don't let this slob</i>

04:13.069 --> 04:14.402
<i> be next to me.</i>

04:14.480 --> 04:15.754
[Comic Book Guy]
<i> God, don't let this slob</i>

04:15.905 --> 04:17.330
<i> be next to me.</i>

04:17.407 --> 04:18.665
[both groan]

04:18.667 --> 04:19.907
Good morning, everyone.

04:19.985 --> 04:21.001
My name is Joel,

04:21.077 --> 04:24.004
and I'll be
your "wingman" today.

04:24.080 --> 04:25.489
[passengers chuckling]

04:25.491 --> 04:26.932
[chuckles] Thank you.

04:26.934 --> 04:30.102
Just a reminder: Federal law
prohibits smoking of any kind,

04:30.178 --> 04:33.087
unless, like me,
you're smokin' hot.

04:33.107 --> 04:34.547
[imitates sizzling]

04:34.625 --> 04:35.999
[chuckling]

04:36.018 --> 04:37.776
Oh, great.

04:37.853 --> 04:40.112
Forced comedy
at 9:00 in the morning.

04:40.188 --> 04:41.280
[video game beeping]

04:41.356 --> 04:43.782
Now, Maggie,
screens turn brains to mush.

04:43.933 --> 04:46.285
That's why Bart has to
take ESL classes.

04:46.361 --> 04:48.954
I'll parent you
how I wanted to be parented,

04:49.031 --> 04:51.865
and sibling you
how I wanted to be sibbled,

04:51.941 --> 04:55.943
with my Jazz Legends
A-to-Z flashcards.

04:56.021 --> 04:57.779
Cannonball Adderley.

04:57.856 --> 05:00.632
He was more
hard bop then bebop.

05:00.634 --> 05:02.208
Okay, movie fans, it's time for

05:02.361 --> 05:04.694
everybody's favorite
in-flight flick,

05:04.696 --> 05:06.120
the safety demo.

05:06.198 --> 05:08.640
Remember this come Oscar time.

05:08.642 --> 05:09.791
[chuckles]

05:09.868 --> 05:10.884
[passengers chuckling weakly]

05:10.960 --> 05:13.036
[groans] Good thing I've got

05:13.038 --> 05:16.206
my annoyance-canceling
headphones.

05:16.208 --> 05:19.300
Ooh, we are really
packed in here, aren't we?

05:19.378 --> 05:22.395
Something is very wrong
with this plane.

05:22.472 --> 05:24.138
-This is a trap!
-[passengers chattering]

05:24.216 --> 05:25.899
It's a conspiracy
to take us down!

05:25.901 --> 05:27.308
-[woman] Get out of here!
-Oh. Oh!

05:27.386 --> 05:28.902
They're experimenting on us!

05:28.904 --> 05:31.404
I won't be a rat
in your flying cage!

05:31.481 --> 05:35.058
Ah, a seat for my second cheek.

05:35.060 --> 05:36.393
Yo, travel trolls.

05:36.395 --> 05:38.395
A crazy lady just
got kicked off the plane

05:38.413 --> 05:41.322
so I jump-squatted
a sweet aisle seat.

05:41.324 --> 05:44.343
Give my 40,000 followers
a moan, bald dude.

05:44.419 --> 05:46.327
D'oh.

05:46.329 --> 05:48.071
[Auto-Tuned voice]
♪<i> D'oh, d'oh</i> ♪

05:48.073 --> 05:49.997
♪<i> D-d-d-d-d-d'oh</i> ♪

05:50.075 --> 05:52.309
♪<i> D-d-d-d-d-d'oh.</i> ♪

05:54.246 --> 05:55.604
[Homer]
Toenail clipper?

05:56.673 --> 05:57.731
Sardine eater?

05:58.767 --> 06:01.084
Disgusto-flossers?

06:01.086 --> 06:02.586
-Hiya!
-[grunts]

06:02.588 --> 06:04.512
Karate children?

06:04.590 --> 06:08.091
Marge, I'm trying
to hold it together,

06:08.093 --> 06:10.443
just like I promised.

06:10.520 --> 06:11.444
[buzzes]

06:11.521 --> 06:14.206
[sighs]

06:15.767 --> 06:18.268
But it seems like
this plane is filled with

06:18.270 --> 06:21.546
all the worst flyers
in the world.

06:21.548 --> 06:23.123
Well, his text was correct,
senator.

06:23.199 --> 06:26.051
Our airline serves
the fastest-growing demographic

06:26.128 --> 06:28.945
in air travel:
the criminally obnoxious.

06:28.947 --> 06:30.222
At Convenience Airways,

06:30.298 --> 06:33.483
<i> we fly the No Fly List.</i>

06:33.485 --> 06:35.352
♪

06:42.144 --> 06:44.051
Mr. Wingspan--
if that is your funny name--

06:44.129 --> 06:45.629
you mean to tell us

06:45.631 --> 06:49.132
that you filled an entire plane
with obnoxious people

06:49.134 --> 06:50.909
who were banned
from other airlines?

06:51.060 --> 06:54.804
Yes. Our business model
is to cater to C.I.F.s:

06:54.806 --> 06:57.231
"Civility Impaired Fliers."

06:57.309 --> 06:59.233
-Hiya!
-Control your team!

06:59.235 --> 07:02.421
Violence is a form of control.

07:02.572 --> 07:04.965
[karate children]
Yes, Sensei. Hiya!

07:05.926 --> 07:07.817
This was our inaugural flight,

07:07.819 --> 07:10.654
testing if the innovative
precautions we had taken

07:10.656 --> 07:15.842
were enough to safely transport
the rudest of the rude.

07:15.919 --> 07:16.843
Like this man.

07:16.845 --> 07:18.662
[Homer] Aw, come on.

07:18.664 --> 07:21.756
You choke out one guy
with a seat belt extender

07:21.833 --> 07:23.090
and you're labeled for life.

07:23.168 --> 07:24.684
But on this flight,

07:24.761 --> 07:26.853
I promised Marge I would behave,

07:26.930 --> 07:28.613
and I really tried.

07:28.690 --> 07:30.097
It was torture.

07:30.099 --> 07:31.450
[Homer]
<i> Torture!</i>

07:31.526 --> 07:32.692
[screams]

07:32.844 --> 07:35.620
Who would do such a thing
to Patrick Wilson?

07:35.772 --> 07:37.998
Eyes on your own screen.

07:39.534 --> 07:40.292
Ugh.

07:40.443 --> 07:42.276
And, no, you may not have any of

07:42.354 --> 07:44.688
my triad of expired
Christmas delights.

07:44.690 --> 07:46.131
Mmm, cheese.

07:46.208 --> 07:48.467
Mmm, butter, caramel...

07:49.669 --> 07:52.637
Mmm. [grunting]

07:52.639 --> 07:54.956
And now,
the shower of champions.

07:55.033 --> 07:56.349
Huzzah.

07:57.460 --> 07:58.727
[shudders]

07:59.796 --> 08:02.055
[coughing]
Come on.

08:02.131 --> 08:03.482
Uh, excuse me.

08:03.484 --> 08:06.226
I promised my wife
I wouldn't fight or yell

08:06.378 --> 08:08.378
or pee anywhere
other than the bathroom,

08:08.380 --> 08:12.306
but this guy next to me
is making it really hard.

08:12.326 --> 08:13.733
What guy?

08:13.810 --> 08:15.719
The Comic Book Guy guy.

08:15.721 --> 08:17.737
Huh? He just disappeared.

08:17.739 --> 08:21.558
Well, it looks like the problem
took care of itself.

08:21.560 --> 08:23.560
That is so weird.

08:23.562 --> 08:26.229
Hey, guys,
you asked for it, I'm doing it.

08:26.231 --> 08:29.749
The bathroom sink
shrimp scampi challenge.

08:29.826 --> 08:31.251
Oh.

08:31.253 --> 08:34.721
<i> Marge, I'm barely holding it</i>
<i> together back here.</i>

08:34.756 --> 08:38.925
<i> Please text me back</i>
<i> some sweet words of comfort.</i>

08:39.002 --> 08:40.227
[buzzes]

08:43.098 --> 08:44.856
[both snoring]

08:44.933 --> 08:47.108
Hey, hey...

08:48.195 --> 08:51.046
-Huzzah...
-Hey, hey...

08:51.122 --> 08:52.989
Zounds...

08:57.445 --> 08:58.778
Oh...

08:58.930 --> 09:00.947
needs tonic.

09:01.024 --> 09:02.874
[slurping]

09:02.951 --> 09:04.617
[video game noises]

09:04.694 --> 09:05.618
[laughs]

09:05.695 --> 09:07.462
Die, die, die!

09:08.607 --> 09:10.698
No, don't die!

09:10.700 --> 09:12.199
They're all dead.

09:12.277 --> 09:14.344
Oh, I need to play something.

09:15.630 --> 09:17.204
-[grunting]
-[beeping]

09:17.282 --> 09:19.040
I'm winning. I'm winning.

09:19.117 --> 09:20.559
Just a reminder, folks,

09:20.635 --> 09:23.469
the call button
is only for real emergencies,

09:23.546 --> 09:26.639
like if you're down to
your last guess on Wordle.

09:26.641 --> 09:28.733
[passengers chuckling]

09:28.810 --> 09:31.477
Uh, I have a real emergency.

09:31.554 --> 09:32.962
Your jokes suck.

09:32.964 --> 09:34.739
[passengers laughing]

09:35.909 --> 09:37.742
"S" is for Sun Ra.

09:37.744 --> 09:39.060
He's a little abstract,

09:39.137 --> 09:42.322
but when you get it,
you'll really get it.

09:42.398 --> 09:44.140
Dig this.

09:44.142 --> 09:46.251
[experimental jazz plays]

09:47.829 --> 09:49.996
[crying]

09:50.073 --> 09:52.498
Somebody shut that brat up!

09:52.617 --> 09:53.758
Oh, that's my brat.

09:53.835 --> 09:54.984
Stop judging her!

09:54.986 --> 09:56.336
I don't know what to do.

09:56.488 --> 09:59.580
I've been turning the jazz up
as loud as I can,

09:59.600 --> 10:01.433
but it's not soothing her.

10:01.509 --> 10:03.751
Is this an airline or a nursery?

10:03.829 --> 10:05.678
Mustn't punch the jerk.

10:05.680 --> 10:06.921
Mustn't punch
the jerk.

10:06.998 --> 10:09.757
It's so loud,
I can barely hear myself

10:09.835 --> 10:11.926
feel up my mistress
under this blanket.

10:12.003 --> 10:13.778
Okay, gang,
we're about to start

10:13.855 --> 10:16.005
our beverage and snack service.

10:16.007 --> 10:17.357
If you feel like a pretzel,

10:17.433 --> 10:18.950
that means
the guy in front of you

10:19.027 --> 10:21.786
has his seat all the way back.

10:21.788 --> 10:23.513
[passengers chuckling]

10:23.515 --> 10:25.698
Just because
it sounds like a joke

10:25.775 --> 10:27.033
doesn't mean it is one.

10:27.110 --> 10:29.869
[passengers laughing]

10:29.946 --> 10:31.445
Come back in ten years, kid.

10:31.523 --> 10:34.540
I got voicemails
older than you. Ha!

10:34.542 --> 10:35.950
[passengers chuckle]

10:36.953 --> 10:40.363
And now it's time
for your headliner. Me!

10:40.365 --> 10:42.307
This guy's jokes suck so hard,

10:42.309 --> 10:44.217
we're about to lose
cabin pressure.

10:44.219 --> 10:45.685
[passengers laughing]

10:46.963 --> 10:49.222
Okay, okay.
People, don't encourage him!

10:49.298 --> 10:51.816
...is what Joel's guidance
counselor told his parents.

10:51.893 --> 10:54.069
[laughter]

10:54.896 --> 10:56.196
Give me that.

10:57.732 --> 10:59.215
[Bart mimicking]
This is your

10:59.217 --> 11:01.217
unfunny flight attendant Joel
speaking.

11:01.219 --> 11:03.903
Here are some more
of my terrible jokes.

11:03.980 --> 11:06.122
-[blows raspberry]
-[mimics farting]

11:10.061 --> 11:11.485
[motorboats]

11:11.487 --> 11:13.505
-[fart sounds continue]
-[passengers laughing]

11:16.510 --> 11:19.068
Left forward lavatory.

11:19.070 --> 11:20.679
-[hollow crash]
-[Bart]<i> Ay, caramba!</i>

11:20.755 --> 11:24.424
-[crying]
-Okay, so Daddy doesn't get
into a fistfight,

11:24.500 --> 11:26.926
we're going to take
a little walk.

11:26.928 --> 11:28.169
[crying]

11:28.171 --> 11:30.689
Dad, I figured out
what's gonna calm Maggie.

11:30.691 --> 11:34.417
Improvisations in the style
of pre-heroin Coltrane.

11:34.419 --> 11:36.419
[playing]

11:36.421 --> 11:38.738
[wailing]

11:41.702 --> 11:43.776
[wails]

11:43.929 --> 11:46.037
Mama!

11:46.039 --> 11:48.598
No, no, we can't bother Mommy...

11:48.600 --> 11:51.192
[singsongy]
...or she'll leave us all
for good.

11:51.194 --> 11:52.293
[Maggie grunts]

11:54.197 --> 11:56.697
Hey, champ, I lost $50,000

11:56.775 --> 11:59.884
on your pay-per-view fight
against Vanilla Ice.

11:59.961 --> 12:01.368
You owe me!

12:01.446 --> 12:06.282
Come on, champ,
I'm talking to you, champ.

12:06.284 --> 12:08.134
Oh, no, my Chekhov's gin.

12:08.136 --> 12:10.228
[slurping loudly]

12:13.567 --> 12:16.550
[groans]
Nobody licks me but my tiger.

12:16.628 --> 12:18.052
[crying]

12:18.129 --> 12:21.072
That baby's
a lap-sitting freeloader.

12:21.149 --> 12:24.317
I am sorry you have
to put up with that guy.

12:24.393 --> 12:26.152
We're all just doing our best.

12:26.229 --> 12:30.323
Yeah. Parents don't get to go
into airplane mode, do we?

12:30.399 --> 12:33.400
Thank God. Two sensible people.

12:33.478 --> 12:34.978
[alarm beeps]

12:34.980 --> 12:37.480
Wylder, it's time.

12:37.499 --> 12:39.665
-[toilet] ♪<i> Let's all sing</i> ♪
-Yeesh.

12:39.742 --> 12:40.817
♪<i> The potty song</i> ♪

12:40.819 --> 12:42.168
Oh, no... No, no, no.

12:42.320 --> 12:45.430
Our little guy is on a strict
potty training schedule.

12:45.507 --> 12:46.656
[playful music playing]

12:46.674 --> 12:49.100
♪<i> When it's time</i>
<i> to make a poo-poo</i> ♪

12:49.102 --> 12:51.585
♪<i> Give a shout, whoo-hoo.</i> ♪

12:51.663 --> 12:53.396
Whoo-hoo!

12:54.833 --> 12:56.257
No hoo!

12:56.334 --> 12:58.276
Um, do you guys have
any diapers?

12:58.427 --> 13:00.520
Uh, we don't use the "D" word.

13:00.596 --> 13:01.838
Oh, boy.

13:01.840 --> 13:04.507
-Deal with your biohazard!
-Change that baby!

13:04.509 --> 13:06.117
-What's wrong with you?
-Oh, come on!

13:06.194 --> 13:08.119
That's not a baby,
that's a hate crime.

13:08.121 --> 13:10.346
Lisa, where's the diaper bag?

13:10.365 --> 13:11.514
I don't have it.

13:11.516 --> 13:14.292
Why don't you ask
your girlfriend, Maggie?

13:14.294 --> 13:16.777
Maggie's not my girlfriend,
Marge is.

13:16.855 --> 13:17.945
[gasps] That's it.

13:18.023 --> 13:20.089
Marge has it.

13:21.209 --> 13:23.968
-[grunting]
-[groaning]

13:24.879 --> 13:26.471
[Homer]
There's the bag.

13:26.548 --> 13:28.548
Maggie, crawl through
the clown fight.

13:28.624 --> 13:30.558
[grunting continues]

13:32.646 --> 13:34.537
Don't kill him, champ.

13:34.539 --> 13:36.539
My pension is almost vested.

13:36.541 --> 13:37.540
[Krusty groans]

13:37.542 --> 13:38.483
[grunting]

13:38.634 --> 13:40.610
♪

13:43.139 --> 13:46.157
Okay, Maggie, to the bathroom.

13:48.553 --> 13:50.453
♪

13:58.897 --> 14:00.338
We made it.

14:01.174 --> 14:03.091
[shrieks] Toilet Chef.

14:04.010 --> 14:05.751
[grunting]

14:05.828 --> 14:07.428
[shrieks] In-laws!

14:08.497 --> 14:11.516
Care to join
our Mile-High Book Club?

14:11.593 --> 14:13.351
[shrieks] Readers!

14:16.414 --> 14:17.763
SunChips. Give me, give me.

14:17.765 --> 14:19.006
[indistinct shouting]

14:19.008 --> 14:20.525
[overlapping arguments]

14:24.756 --> 14:26.364
[both exhale loudly]

14:27.850 --> 14:30.326
What the...?

14:32.947 --> 14:34.539
Where is everybody?

14:34.616 --> 14:37.433
Please calmly return
to your seat, sir.

14:37.435 --> 14:39.785
What did you do with all
the horrible people I hate?

14:39.862 --> 14:41.045
Tell me what's going on.

14:41.197 --> 14:42.863
Or I'll seatbelt you good.

14:42.941 --> 14:45.274
And why don't they make
the whole plane out of the...

14:45.293 --> 14:48.111
-black box material...?
-[thuds]

14:48.129 --> 14:49.462
[pilot]
<i> This is your captain speaking.</i>

14:49.614 --> 14:51.814
<i> If you look to your left,</i>
<i> you will see</i>

14:51.816 --> 14:53.558
<i> the magnificent Grand Canyon.</i>

14:53.635 --> 14:58.621
<i> Unless you're one of the 246</i>
<i> unruly souls who've been</i>

14:58.623 --> 15:02.901
<i> trap-doored into our</i>
<i>complimentary in-flight prison.</i>

15:02.977 --> 15:04.444
[moans sadly]

15:09.892 --> 15:11.659
[saxophone playing]

15:14.155 --> 15:17.640
Trapdoors that lead to a prison?
Since when?

15:17.642 --> 15:20.977
What monster could conceive
of something this horrible?

15:20.979 --> 15:22.420
BurnsCo.

15:22.497 --> 15:25.998
<i> Proudly installing trapdoor</i>
<i> dungeon drops since 1926.</i>

15:26.075 --> 15:27.817
Is there anything
more satisfying

15:27.835 --> 15:30.987
than a scream of terror
followed by a distant thud?

15:30.989 --> 15:32.931
Mr. Wingspan, this is America.

15:32.933 --> 15:35.099
When we violate
people's civil liberties,

15:35.176 --> 15:38.177
we usually give them a heads-up,
drop pamphlets,

15:38.254 --> 15:40.587
send a cruise missile,
uh, something.

15:40.665 --> 15:44.333
Senator, I assure you,
we did warn the passengers

15:44.335 --> 15:47.278
of the potential consequences
of their actions.

15:47.430 --> 15:49.781
It's all in the safety video.

15:49.857 --> 15:51.932
But nobody watches those things.

15:52.010 --> 15:54.077
[murmured agreements]

15:55.346 --> 15:56.512
[alert chimes]

15:56.605 --> 15:58.439
[announcer]
<i>Should you choose to be unruly,</i>

15:58.441 --> 16:02.126
<i> you'll be trap-doored into</i>
<i> our belly-of-the-plane prison.</i>

16:02.128 --> 16:04.611
<i>If your behavior is too extreme,</i>

16:04.689 --> 16:06.965
<i> a ball gag will fall</i>
<i> from the ceiling.</i>

16:07.041 --> 16:09.116
<i> Please affix your own</i>
<i> ball gag first</i>

16:09.118 --> 16:11.970
<i>before ball-gagging your child.</i>

16:12.046 --> 16:13.787
See? I was right.

16:13.865 --> 16:16.457
I tried to warn you,
but you all thought I was crazy.

16:16.534 --> 16:19.869
Not to criticize,
but maybe it's your tone?

16:19.887 --> 16:21.704
My tone is fine!

16:21.706 --> 16:23.106
[gagging]

16:24.300 --> 16:26.726
And that concludes
your beverage service.

16:26.802 --> 16:28.711
[passengers chuckling]

16:28.730 --> 16:30.637
[muffled]
He's pretty funny.

16:30.639 --> 16:32.715
No, he's not, he sucks.

16:32.734 --> 16:34.108
[Joel]
Take that!

16:34.219 --> 16:36.160
-[laughs, whoops]
-[coughs]

16:36.162 --> 16:37.887
They can't do this to us!

16:37.889 --> 16:41.165
Buying a ticket gives us
the right to do what we want.

16:41.317 --> 16:43.650
There's no law in the sky.

16:43.728 --> 16:45.578
I say we bust out.

16:45.654 --> 16:46.912
Who's with me?

16:46.914 --> 16:49.081
[excited agreements]

16:49.234 --> 16:51.825
We'll need
every available weapon.

16:51.903 --> 16:54.679
I got toenail clippers.
And some pretty sharp toenails.

16:54.756 --> 16:58.474
I got an airsick bag
of hot bathroom shrimp.

17:00.094 --> 17:01.744
[Homer]
<i> My darling Marge.</i>

17:01.746 --> 17:04.597
<i> I am writing you from the cusp</i>
<i> of yet another prison riot.</i>

17:04.599 --> 17:07.025
<i> If I die in this heroic</i>
<i> escape attempt,</i>

17:07.027 --> 17:08.751
<i> remember me</i>
<i> as a blameless victim.</i>

17:08.753 --> 17:12.346
<i> One who got caught up</i>
<i>in the coach-to-prison pipeline.</i>

17:12.348 --> 17:14.757
<i> BTW, lost Maggie,</i>
<i> hope she's with you.</i>

17:14.759 --> 17:17.184
<i> -Lots going on. Shrug emoji.</i>
-[chicken clucks]

17:17.262 --> 17:19.328
[snoring lightly]

17:22.433 --> 17:24.375
[cooing]

17:25.378 --> 17:27.378
[babbling]

17:28.364 --> 17:30.531
Marge is writing me back.

17:30.608 --> 17:32.699
Stop? Stop what?

17:32.719 --> 17:35.219
Wine, wine, wine?

17:35.296 --> 17:37.463
Do you want me to stop whining?

17:37.540 --> 17:39.465
[giggles]

17:39.542 --> 17:41.467
[Homer]
Bee. Man.

17:41.469 --> 17:43.119
Be a man?

17:43.121 --> 17:44.954
X. Lobster.

17:44.956 --> 17:47.123
Don't be shellfish?

17:47.141 --> 17:50.717
Oh, my God, I am always
thinking of my shelf.

17:50.719 --> 17:52.886
[all chanting]
Window seat.

17:52.964 --> 17:56.299
Window seat. Window seat.

17:56.301 --> 17:58.559
No! This revolt is wrong.

17:58.636 --> 18:00.894
I know this because my wife
just spoke to me

18:00.972 --> 18:04.064
in a series of direct
and unambiguous emojis.

18:04.066 --> 18:07.159
Let us not be pigs. Or mules.

18:07.236 --> 18:09.403
Or a mermaid with a fax machine.

18:09.480 --> 18:11.572
Sure, we have to put up
with baggage fees,

18:11.649 --> 18:16.485
no leg room, and those
$20 "protein boxes."

18:16.487 --> 18:19.488
But flying is a modern miracle,

18:19.490 --> 18:22.916
and all that's
asked of us in return

18:22.994 --> 18:26.829
is basic human decency.

18:26.831 --> 18:28.681
[quiet murmuring]

18:28.757 --> 18:31.943
Mm, I could be more patient
with kids and babies.

18:32.019 --> 18:34.687
After all,
I am a preschool teacher.

18:34.689 --> 18:38.023
I'm sorry I savagely beat your
husband with your hair bone.

18:38.100 --> 18:40.934
[stammers]
He's not my...

18:40.954 --> 18:42.936
Oh, forget it.

18:43.014 --> 18:44.771
So to quote my wife,

18:44.849 --> 18:47.291
we have to start
acting civilized

18:47.368 --> 18:51.370
and stop being
a bunch of huge...

18:51.447 --> 18:53.172
eggplants.

18:54.692 --> 18:56.467
[pilot]
<i> Well, folks,</i>
<i> now that you've exhibited</i>

18:56.544 --> 18:58.136
<i> a modicum of civility,</i>

18:58.212 --> 18:59.971
<i> the handcuff sign has been</i>
<i> turned off.</i>

19:00.047 --> 19:02.456
<i> You are now free to return</i>
<i> to your seats</i>

19:02.458 --> 19:04.200
<i> and work through</i>
<i> the childhood trauma</i>

19:04.202 --> 19:05.959
<i> that led you to behave</i>
<i> like the ugliest</i>

19:06.037 --> 19:08.312
<i> of ugly Americans today.</i>

19:08.314 --> 19:11.357
♪

19:15.989 --> 19:17.471
Excuse me, Mrs. Simpson.

19:17.548 --> 19:19.382
We'll be landing soon,
so we need you

19:19.384 --> 19:21.492
to return your seat
to its upright position.

19:21.569 --> 19:24.478
[groans softly]
What? We're landing?

19:24.555 --> 19:28.166
I slept through
my first first class?

19:28.242 --> 19:31.911
Yes, but you got the most
perfect flying experience

19:31.913 --> 19:33.579
anyone could ever ask for.

19:33.581 --> 19:36.823
You didn't even know
you were on a plane.

19:36.825 --> 19:38.250
Aw.

19:38.327 --> 19:43.497
And then she gave me the best
cookie of my entire life.

19:43.574 --> 19:45.832
Aw, cookie.

19:45.910 --> 19:49.503
After listening to the 14 hours
of testimony today,

19:49.522 --> 19:52.172
I propose
that Convenience Airways'

19:52.250 --> 19:55.768
radical passenger control system
be approved for use

19:55.844 --> 19:58.270
across the entire
airline industry.

19:58.347 --> 19:59.680
-Hear! Hear!
-Yes.

19:59.757 --> 20:00.681
I agree.

20:00.758 --> 20:02.258
Well, I say, trap-door them all

20:02.260 --> 20:04.593
and let the FAA sort it out.

20:04.595 --> 20:05.761
Excellent.

20:05.763 --> 20:07.705
-So ordered.
-Wait.

20:07.856 --> 20:11.116
As the one person who was
not trap-doored on this flight,

20:11.235 --> 20:13.544
I believe I have
the authority to say

20:13.546 --> 20:18.290
that mass in-flight
incarceration is not the answer.

20:18.367 --> 20:20.534
We need thoughtful solutions

20:20.536 --> 20:23.870
to this epidemic of rudeness
and disrespect.

20:23.948 --> 20:25.556
Sure, it's easy to push a button

20:25.633 --> 20:28.375
and drop all your problems
down a trap...

20:28.377 --> 20:30.728
door...!

20:30.805 --> 20:32.638
-[thuds]
-Ow!

20:32.715 --> 20:35.233
Honey, are you hurt?

20:35.309 --> 20:38.385
[Marge echoing]
I'm okay. I landed on my hair.

